oai_dc:dc.dc:date: Carbon dating results: The papyrus was produced between 574 and 660 with a margin of certainty of 95.4 %; between 608 and 650 with a margin of 68.2 %.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Remains of a receipt for the payment of wheat and maybe money for the annona. Translation: Village of Tertembuthis embole … through Menas for adaeratio two artabae of wheat, in total 2 artabae of wheat. And for your surety I have made this complete receipt as above written. … Tertembuthis … Menas, assistant, I agree and wrote (?) …
oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Receipt for the payment of wheat (and money?)
